msgstr ""

msgid "How it works — Ski Parrainage"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Two things carry a status here, and it helps to keep them apart: your "
"registration, and a match. You always have exactly one registration — your "
"own standing in the system. Over a season you might be part of several "
"matches, since an early one can fall through and you go back in the queue to "
"be paired again."
msgstr ""

msgid "Part 1 — Your registration"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Your registration is your place in the system — the answer to \"am I in the "
"queue, waiting to be matched?\""
msgstr ""

msgid "Status"
msgstr ""

msgid "What it means"
msgstr ""

msgid "What happens next"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You've signed up but haven't confirmed your email address yet. You are not "
"in the queue."
msgstr ""

msgid "Click the link in the confirmation email. That moves you to Verified."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You're active and in the queue, waiting to be matched (or already in an "
"active match)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The system pairs you with an eligible partner as soon as one is available. "
"When it does, a match is created."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You declined a match, or didn't respond in time, so you've been taken out of "
"the queue. Nothing is lost — your registration is kept."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Go to your account page and choose \"Rejoin the queue\". That moves you back "
"to Verified and you'll be matched again."
msgstr ""

msgid "You chose to leave the programme."
msgstr ""

msgid "Nothing further. You can register again if you change your mind."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You were reported as a no-show after a match was confirmed, so you've been "
"removed from the pool."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This is set by programme staff via the report process, not something you "
"undo yourself. Contact the programme if you think it's a mistake."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In short: Verified is the healthy, waiting state. Everything else is either "
"a step before it (Unverified) or a step out of the pool (Paused, Withdrawn, "
"Suspended). Only Paused has a self-service way back in."
msgstr ""

msgid "Part 2 — A match"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Once you're Verified and a suitable partner is available, the system creates "
"a match — a pairing of one Ambassador and one Referee. You don't choose your "
"partner; the system assigns one, and both of you are notified. From that "
"moment there is a contact window — its length is shown in the match email — "
"in which both of you must accept. Until you both accept, you can each see "
"the other person's first name, but not their email or phone number: contact "
"details are revealed only once both sides have accepted. This is deliberate "
"— it's the core privacy promise of the service."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You've just been paired. Neither of you has accepted yet. You can see your "
"partner's first name only."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Accept within the contact window. If your partner accepts first, you'll see "
"the match move to Pending."
msgstr ""

msgid "One of you has accepted; the system is waiting on the other."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The second person accepts and the match becomes Accepted. If the window runs "
"out with only one acceptance, it becomes Expired."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Both of you accepted. Contact details are now revealed. This is the success "
"state."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Get in touch with your partner and go make your application together — this "
"happens off the app."
msgstr ""

msgid "One of you declined the pairing."
